node.text:
Layers is a 4K digital art film directed by Maxim Zhestkov exploring the juxtaposition of the outside and inside. Computer-generated dark and brutal geometric monoliths are dissected by invisible 3D objects to reveal the layers of the colourful and emotionally vibrant inner structures. At the intersections of the shapes we encounter complex structures which could be perceived as 3D representations of objects within a 4D universe.

After the previous art films’ foray into the territory of imaginary gallery spaces (Elements and Volumes), Maxim decided to push further and explore the possibilities of impossible sculptures as the main character for this project.

Layers is the fourth film in the series which Maxim launched in 2017. Maxim has committed to producing one film each season for the rest of his life along with commercial projects in his studio - Zhestkov.Studio - to express his thoughts, ideas and vision and to explore new boundaries of digital art.

https://zhestkov.studio/

node.text:
Optics is an experimental art film by Maxim Zhestkov exploring the behaviour of artificial light and colour in digital environments. Blending architectural gallery space with computer-generated digital glass sculptures, we encounter animated refractions, chromatic aberrations, colourful reflection and other conditions which are impossible in reality. A series of tests and explorations guides us through different optical conditions of the bright and colourful digital universe.

Website - zhestkov.com/#/optics
Instagram - instagram.com/zhestkov/
Behance -behance.net/gallery/69664253/Optics-Art-film

Designed and directed by Maxim Zhestkov / zhestkov.com
Sound Design by Marcelo Baldin / combustion.studio

node.text:
Elements is an experimental art film by Maxim Zhestkov about nature, physics, art and love.
More than 2 billion elements / particles governed by tensions and forces of nature were used to tell stories and show emotions through the motion of collective behavior. The film is a trial to explore the idea that everything around us and inside us is made from simple elements / blocks which can be arranged in complex relationships and become compound structures.
We could project this idea into emotions, behaviours, thought processes, relationships, life, planets and the universe.
http://www.zhestkov.com/elements

node.title: Elements - Art film by Maxim Zhestkov

The energy of magnetic field lines created by a powerful charge that transforms the space around it. This is my collaboration with @bmw in which I worked with the theme of electric energy, one of the most fundamental forces of nature. Activated by a brand new electric BMW i4 from the @bmwi series, the installation reacts to the energy flow and changes its shape, illuminated by bright flashes of electricity. 

#THEi4 #BMW #BMWi #BornElectric #zhestkov #electricity #energy

At @media.work, we don't just explore digital realities, we are a team of creators with background in industrial design, architecture, interior design and fashion. Through digital, we study how materials, light, and movement work on real life. We don't aim for a flawless look, we search true meanings and experiences, represented in nuances and imperfections of objects. Together with our industrial designers, we produce virtual objects and installations that test the boundary between physical and digital. Here is one of our experiments with glass.

#mediawork #glass #material #digital #design

node.text:
Together with @bmw, we created an art exploration of electromagnetic phenomena, lying at the heart of the brand's new electric model i4. Electric forces connect our world on many levels: from attraction of subatomic particles to signals from distant stars coming to Earth as electromagnetic waves. Interpreting these physical phenomena, I made three virtual installations. 

This one shows electricity through the movement of particles between two poles activated by the car, energy of ignition visualized.

@BMWi
